IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
       PROGRAM-ID. FileReadTemplate.
       AUTHOR.     YourName.
       DATE-WRITTEN. Today.

       ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
       INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
       FILE-CONTROL.
      * Map the internal file name (INPUT-FILE) to the physical file on disk.
      * "input.txt" can be a static path or mapped via JCL/Environment variables.
           SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO "input.dat"
               ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL
               FILE STATUS IS WS-FILE-STATUS.

       DATA DIVISION.
       FILE SECTION.
       FD  INPUT-FILE.
      * Define the record layout of the file here.
       01  INPUT-RECORD.
           05  IN-ID           PIC 9(05).
           05  IN-NAME         PIC X(20).
           05  IN-AMOUNT       PIC 9(05)V99.
           05  FILLER          PIC X(50).

       WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
      * Variables for file status handling
       01  WS-FILE-STATUS      PIC X(02).
           88  FS-OK           VALUE "00".
           88  FS-EOF          VALUE "10".

      * Switches/Flags
       01  WS-EOF-FLAG         PIC X(01) VALUE 'N'.
           88  END-OF-FILE     VALUE 'Y'.

      * Counters (Optional)
       01  WS-RECORD-COUNT     PIC 9(05) VALUE 0.

       PROCEDURE DIVISION.
       000-MAIN-LOGIC.
           PERFORM 100-INITIALIZE
           PERFORM 200-PROCESS-FILE
           PERFORM 300-CLEANUP
           STOP RUN.

       100-INITIALIZE.
           DISPLAY "Program Started."
           
           OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
           
           IF NOT FS-OK
               DISPLAY "Error opening file. Status: " WS-FILE-STATUS
               MOVE 'Y' TO WS-EOF-FLAG
           ELSE
               PERFORM 150-READ-RECORD
           END-IF.

       150-READ-RECORD.
           READ INPUT-FILE
               AT END
                   MOVE 'Y' TO WS-EOF-FLAG
               NOT AT END
                   ADD 1 TO WS-RECORD-COUNT
           END-READ.

       200-PROCESS-FILE.
      * The standard loop: Perform until the EOF flag is set to Yes
           PERFORM UNTIL END-OF-FILE
               
               PERFORM 250-HANDLE-DATA
               
               PERFORM 150-READ-RECORD
           END-PERFORM.

       250-HANDLE-DATA.
      * -------------------------------------------------------
      * YOUR BUSINESS LOGIC GOES HERE
      * -------------------------------------------------------
           DISPLAY "Processing Record #" WS-RECORD-COUNT 
           DISPLAY "ID: " IN-ID " Name: " IN-NAME
           .

       300-CLEANUP.
           IF WS-FILE-STATUS = "00" OR "10"
               CLOSE INPUT-FILE
           END-IF
           
           DISPLAY "Program Finished."
           DISPLAY "Total Records Processed: " WS-RECORD-COUNT.